physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and interactive. In no acute distress. HEENT: NCAT. PERRL, EOMI. Sclera anicteric and without injection. MMM. NECK: No cervical lymphadenopathy. CARDIAC: Regular rhythm, normal rate. Audible S1 and S2. No murmurs/rubs/gallops. LUNGS: Clear to auscultation bilaterally. No wheezes, rhonchi or rales. No increased work of breathing. BACK: No spinous process tenderness. No CVA tenderness. ABDOMEN: Soft, non distended, non-tender to deep palpation in all four quadrants. EXTREMITIES: No clubbing, cyanosis, or edema. Pulses DP/Radial 2+ bilaterally. SKIN: Warm. No rash. NEUROLOGIC: Strength throughout normal.
